WEBVTT

00:02.236 --> 00:04.704
[Superbus'
"Invincible and Reckless"]

00:04.771 --> 00:07.541
SINGER:
♪♪ I'm under your spell ♪♪

00:07.608 --> 00:09.009
♪♪ But I'm okay ♪♪

00:09.076 --> 00:11.311
♪♪ You dance it so well ♪♪

00:11.378 --> 00:12.779
♪♪ Don't go away ♪♪

00:12.846 --> 00:15.315
♪♪ I-I'm under your spell ♪♪

00:15.382 --> 00:17.250
♪♪ But I'm okay ♪♪

00:17.317 --> 00:19.253
♪♪ It's magical, physical ♪♪

00:19.320 --> 00:22.188
♪♪ Never gonna give up now ♪♪

00:22.255 --> 00:26.727
♪♪ Invincible, invincible ♪♪

00:26.793 --> 00:29.796
♪♪ And reckless symphony ♪♪

00:29.863 --> 00:32.199
♪♪ I'm under your spell ♪♪

00:32.266 --> 00:34.000
♪♪ But I'm okay ♪♪

00:34.067 --> 00:36.103
♪♪ You dance it so well ♪♪

00:36.170 --> 00:37.737
♪♪ Don't go away ♪♪

00:37.804 --> 00:40.507
♪♪ I-I'm under your spell ♪♪

00:40.574 --> 00:42.109
♪♪ But I'm okay ♪♪

00:42.176 --> 00:43.743
♪♪ It's magical ♪♪

00:46.646 --> 00:48.448
CECE:
Previously on Spellbound...

00:48.515 --> 00:50.283
ADRIAN: I need to figure out
where I'm gonna find

00:50.350 --> 00:53.587
enough Wizens in the same
place at the same time

00:53.653 --> 00:55.188
and cast it
without them knowing.

00:55.255 --> 00:57.024
Cece wrote her intention.

00:57.090 --> 00:59.493
She's crafted
the perfect Wizen circle.

00:59.560 --> 01:01.428
If they're going
to perform this,

01:01.495 --> 01:03.230
I can use it
to build your escape.

01:03.296 --> 01:05.398
- Lizzie's always been
so intuitive.

01:05.465 --> 01:06.600
She knows.

01:06.666 --> 01:08.068
- Back in the day,
Shakespeare was at

01:08.135 --> 01:10.070
some old-timey open mic night

01:10.137 --> 01:11.738
and stole
this woman's entire set.

01:11.805 --> 01:14.241
- When he stole her act,
she cursed the play.

01:14.308 --> 01:15.842
- The person that cast
this curse,

01:15.909 --> 01:17.611
are they a Wizen?
- We're not sure.

01:17.678 --> 01:19.146
- Does this mean
what I think it does?

01:19.213 --> 01:20.981
- She wasn't just
a travelling nomad.

01:21.048 --> 01:23.550
She was a Wizen!
- [giggles]

01:23.617 --> 01:26.553
JULIET: With the pricking
of my thumbs,

01:26.620 --> 01:30.690
something wicked
this way comes.

01:31.825 --> 01:33.026
[gasps]

01:36.630 --> 01:39.700
[chuckling]

01:39.766 --> 01:42.136
[echoing]
Little Wizen,

01:42.203 --> 01:44.938
don't be afraid.

01:45.005 --> 01:50.176
You won't remember
beyond today!

01:50.243 --> 01:51.612
[cackling]

01:51.678 --> 01:53.046
- [gasps]

01:54.381 --> 01:55.882
- Cece, you better get moving.

01:55.949 --> 01:57.017
It's half an hour to warm-up.

01:57.083 --> 01:59.319
- What just happened?

01:59.386 --> 02:00.654
How did I get here?

02:00.721 --> 02:01.755
Where's Amy?

02:01.822 --> 02:03.390
- Come on, get up, sleepyhead.

02:03.457 --> 02:05.492
Today's the day.
[door opens]

02:05.559 --> 02:06.827
- What day?

02:06.894 --> 02:07.962
Performance day?

02:08.028 --> 02:10.030
SIMONE:
Um, yeah.

02:10.096 --> 02:11.298
- No.

02:11.365 --> 02:12.600
I was just
at that creepy theater.

02:12.666 --> 02:14.334
- Did you just have
a stress dream?

02:14.401 --> 02:15.970
- Oh, please.
She's just trying

02:16.036 --> 02:17.871
to throw us off our game.

02:17.938 --> 02:19.573
But it's not happening.

02:19.640 --> 02:21.107
Not today.

02:22.809 --> 02:24.812
[magical warbling]

02:24.878 --> 02:25.846
- Hey.

02:25.912 --> 02:27.314
BOTH: Hey.
AMY: Well?

02:27.381 --> 02:28.749
- Did you guys find
anything good?

02:28.815 --> 02:31.284
- Other than delicious
croissants, nothing.

02:31.351 --> 02:33.187
You?
- No, nothing.

02:33.253 --> 02:35.655
- Seriously, my future
at this school

02:35.722 --> 02:37.023
rides on this show.

02:37.090 --> 02:38.359
I should be spending
my time rehearsing,

02:38.425 --> 02:40.361
not running around trying
to solve this.

02:40.427 --> 02:41.528
I'm done.

02:41.595 --> 02:42.830
- She's not wrong.

02:42.896 --> 02:43.831
Come on, let's bounce.

02:43.898 --> 02:44.832
We have rehearsal.

02:44.899 --> 02:47.802
[tense music]

02:47.868 --> 02:50.671
[magical jingling]

02:50.737 --> 02:52.873
CECE:
This is really weird.

02:52.940 --> 02:55.842
- I'm telling you, I just got
off the phone with her,

02:55.909 --> 02:57.077
and she's the worst.

02:57.144 --> 02:58.445
- If she's that bad,

02:58.512 --> 03:00.580
why are you video-chatting her
every day?

03:00.647 --> 03:03.416
- Hello? Because I saw her
in that fountain.

03:03.483 --> 03:05.352
I need to see her face
every single day

03:05.418 --> 03:07.621
to make sure I know
she's still clueless.

03:07.688 --> 03:08.923
- She can't be that bad.

03:08.989 --> 03:10.257
- Trust me when I tell you,

03:10.324 --> 03:12.926
my sister is a monster.

03:12.993 --> 03:15.529
- Grr!
[laughter]

03:15.596 --> 03:17.097
- That's true.

03:17.164 --> 03:19.366
LIZZIE: [roaring]
- [screams]

03:19.433 --> 03:20.834
- [panting] Lizzie?

03:20.901 --> 03:22.369
- Hello, Ginger.

03:22.436 --> 03:24.204
- What are you doing here?

03:24.271 --> 03:27.741
♪♪ ♪♪

03:27.808 --> 03:29.810
LIZZIE: You seemed
so intense this morning,

03:29.877 --> 03:31.478
I thought I'd check in.

03:31.544 --> 03:33.147
- But we said you wouldn't use
the broom closet

03:33.214 --> 03:34.381
in case Cece was here--

03:34.448 --> 03:36.116
not unless it was an emergency.

03:36.183 --> 03:37.584
- I knew Cece would be
at school.

03:37.651 --> 03:38.819
And it is, isn't it?

03:38.886 --> 03:40.320
An emergency?

03:40.387 --> 03:42.356
- Oh, dear.
Witches brew in paradise.

03:42.422 --> 03:45.126
- Make us some truth tea.

03:45.192 --> 03:46.726
- Whoa, whoa, whoa, whoa!

03:46.793 --> 03:48.361
LIZZIE: I am not leaving
until everything,

03:48.428 --> 03:51.098
and I mean everything,
is on the table.

03:51.165 --> 03:53.634
- Fine.
On one condition.

03:53.701 --> 03:58.739
You have to be nice to Lola
and Amy, my apprentices.

03:58.805 --> 04:00.207
- So nice to meet you.

04:00.274 --> 04:01.875
Now get out.

04:01.942 --> 04:03.844
- [softly] Yeah.
LOLA AND AMY: [gasp]

04:03.911 --> 04:08.782
♪♪ ♪♪

04:08.849 --> 04:10.250
SINGER: ♪♪ Brand-new flavor ♪♪

04:10.317 --> 04:11.819
♪♪ You know what,
yes they know it's major ♪♪

04:11.886 --> 04:13.654
♪♪ I don't wanna rush things
you can savor ♪♪

04:13.721 --> 04:16.156
♪♪ You were like this,
but I'm a lifesaver ♪♪

04:16.223 --> 04:17.458
♪♪ Came here to get it ♪♪

04:17.524 --> 04:19.359
- Hey!
- Whoa, whoa, whoa. You okay?

04:19.426 --> 04:22.162
- Sorry, I don't think
we've been formally introduced.

04:22.229 --> 04:24.031
- I'm Adrian.

04:24.098 --> 04:26.366
- [chuckles]
Is this thing on?

04:26.433 --> 04:28.402
Ladies and gents,
I'd like you to meet Finn.

04:28.468 --> 04:29.603
ADRIAN: [chuckles]
That's a good one.

04:29.670 --> 04:30.738
I was, uh, dropping off

04:30.804 --> 04:32.772
some good-luck gift baskets
from W,

04:32.839 --> 04:34.741
a gift from Cece's aunt Ginger.

04:34.808 --> 04:36.644
- Oh, that's--that's so sweet.

04:36.710 --> 04:39.379
So sorry for running you down.
ADRIAN: Nah, that's fine.

04:39.446 --> 04:41.815
- I need to go, so--
I've gotta rehearse.

04:41.882 --> 04:44.051
- Yeah.
I won't keep you.

04:44.118 --> 04:45.052
- [chuckles]

04:45.119 --> 04:46.753
♪♪ ♪♪

04:46.820 --> 04:48.188
[laughs]

04:48.255 --> 04:49.957
They must've moved that
two inches to the right.

04:50.023 --> 04:50.957
- Mm.

04:51.024 --> 04:53.960
[soft dramatic music]

04:54.027 --> 05:01.201
♪♪ ♪♪

05:15.849 --> 05:17.784
Off you go, then.

05:32.766 --> 05:35.235
- So that was pretty sweet,
what Jack did for Mia, right?

05:35.302 --> 05:36.503
I mean, he got her

05:36.570 --> 05:37.671
her favorite crisps
from Ireland.

05:37.738 --> 05:39.206
Who doesn't love crisps?

05:39.273 --> 05:41.342
- Totally super sweet.
- I know.

05:41.408 --> 05:42.743
I can't think of it too much
today, though,

05:42.810 --> 05:44.545
because it causes
too much inner turmoil,

05:44.612 --> 05:46.113
but I can schedule
a debrief tomorrow,

05:46.179 --> 05:48.048
say, around 3:00 p.m.-ish?
- Not a chance.

05:48.115 --> 05:49.115
I'm only using
this friendly voice

05:49.182 --> 05:50.550
to try and keep Cece calm.

05:50.617 --> 05:52.152
But she didn't hear
a word you said earlier,

05:52.219 --> 05:53.420
so pencil her in.

05:53.487 --> 05:54.755
You can tell her
the whole story again.

05:54.822 --> 05:57.391
- Done.
Warmup in T-minus 22 minutes.

05:57.457 --> 06:00.093
- [sighs]

06:00.160 --> 06:01.562
Come on.

06:01.629 --> 06:03.296
ADRIAN:
Okay, walk through it with me.

06:03.363 --> 06:04.698
I've got the Wizessence,

06:04.764 --> 06:06.300
which gives me access
to the Wizen magic.

06:06.366 --> 06:08.268
I've memorized
the counter spell to banish

06:08.335 --> 06:10.070
that I found
in the book of Jones.

06:10.136 --> 06:11.905
I have all the ingredients.

06:11.972 --> 06:13.040
- Should we practice it?

06:13.107 --> 06:14.808
- No.
KEVIN: Come on.

06:14.875 --> 06:17.644
It would be my joy to see you
acting like a Wizen.

06:17.711 --> 06:19.146
[chuckles]
ADRIAN: Thanks to Cece

06:19.213 --> 06:20.648
and the Paris Opera
Ballet School,

06:20.714 --> 06:23.350
there'll be a Wizen circle
right on stage.

06:23.417 --> 06:25.752
[chuckles] I snuck
into their dress rehearsal,

06:25.819 --> 06:27.154
so I know the exact moment

06:27.220 --> 06:29.556
that she'll be in the center
of the circle.

06:29.623 --> 06:30.958
- Wait, dancers?

06:31.024 --> 06:33.227
- I took over this pedestrian,
Finn.

06:33.293 --> 06:35.763
He's making sure
every one of Cece's classmates

06:35.829 --> 06:38.798
uses their W roll-ons
before going onto stage.

06:38.865 --> 06:39.933
[chuckles]

06:40.000 --> 06:41.134
There's enough Wizessence
in there

06:41.201 --> 06:43.003
to turn
the whole third division

06:43.069 --> 06:45.472
into good, little Wizens.

06:45.538 --> 06:47.608
- [chuckling] Oh, I get it.

06:47.674 --> 06:51.679
You're forming a coven
on stage with Cece.

06:51.746 --> 06:54.981
Okay, I didn't see that coming.
That's awesome!

06:55.048 --> 06:56.383
- Right?

06:56.449 --> 06:57.918
The pedestrian puppet
will make sure

06:57.984 --> 06:59.720
everything goes smoothly.

06:59.786 --> 07:02.023
- I can't believe
I didn't think of it.

07:02.089 --> 07:04.190
It's brilliant!

07:07.127 --> 07:10.063
[flowing classical music]

07:10.130 --> 07:13.333
♪♪ ♪♪

07:13.400 --> 07:15.235
- I can't believe
I freaked out in class.

07:15.302 --> 07:18.939
I'm so humiliated.

07:19.006 --> 07:20.474
My mom cancelled.

07:20.540 --> 07:21.408
- I know.

07:21.475 --> 07:23.543
Jack told me.
I'm sorry.

07:23.610 --> 07:26.046
- I just couldn't
keep it together.

07:26.113 --> 07:28.181
[sighs]
Thanks for the flowers, though.

07:28.248 --> 07:29.550
You really shouldn't have.

07:29.616 --> 07:31.185
- Mm, I didn't.

07:31.251 --> 07:33.688
- Okay, well,
maybe you should have.

07:33.754 --> 07:34.988
- But I didn't.

07:35.055 --> 07:38.759
- Hey there, Lady M and Sir M.

07:38.825 --> 07:40.293
I'm already warmed up.

07:40.360 --> 07:42.229
Can I run those flowers
down to the dressing room?

07:42.295 --> 07:43.431
[whispers]
I need to keep warm.

07:43.497 --> 07:46.000
- Sure. Thanks.
They're for Cece.

07:46.066 --> 07:48.002
- Duh.
You don't say?

07:48.068 --> 07:49.737
[chuckles]
Okay, I'm gonna go,

07:49.803 --> 07:51.538
so I'll see you guys in there,
yeah?

07:51.605 --> 07:52.940
Bye.

07:53.006 --> 07:55.775
- [chuckling] Wow, he's
really high-energy tonight.

07:55.842 --> 07:57.444
- Yeah.
BOTH: [chuckle]

07:57.511 --> 08:04.551
♪♪ ♪♪

08:06.687 --> 08:09.623
[suspenseful music]

08:09.690 --> 08:16.730
♪♪ ♪♪

08:40.688 --> 08:45.426
CECE: Stay with the calm
and steady your thoughts.

08:45.492 --> 08:48.128
Everything is cool.
[exhales deeply]

08:48.195 --> 08:53.233
Let all negative thoughts
wash away.

08:53.300 --> 08:55.235
Just keep breathing.

08:55.302 --> 09:02.342
♪♪ ♪♪

09:02.943 --> 09:04.144
[gasps]

09:06.280 --> 09:07.748
SIMONE:
Hey, what are you doing?

09:07.815 --> 09:09.716
CECE: I'm coming.

09:09.783 --> 09:13.520
SIMONE: [sighs]
You don't have to use magic.

09:13.587 --> 09:15.689
Trust in all the work
you've done.

09:15.756 --> 09:17.457
- I do.
I trust.

09:17.524 --> 09:21.629
I'm not using magic,
I'm clearing my energy.

09:21.695 --> 09:23.230
I keep feeling weird.

09:23.297 --> 09:27.734
I have to make sure the curse
stays very far away.

09:27.801 --> 09:29.937
But something feels off,

09:30.003 --> 09:31.338
and my Wizen instinct
says it's bad.

09:31.405 --> 09:32.773
- It's not.
I promise.

09:32.840 --> 09:35.575
I read our cards,
and it's victories all around.

09:35.642 --> 09:37.978
Just think
about how great our lives are.

09:38.045 --> 09:39.913
A year, we didn't even
know each other.

09:39.980 --> 09:41.415
And now we're best friends

09:41.481 --> 09:43.951
about to dance
on the stage together.

09:44.017 --> 09:46.953
- You're totally right.
I need to stop freaking out.

09:47.020 --> 09:49.857
- It's just nerves.

09:49.924 --> 09:51.358
- Might be nerves.

09:51.425 --> 09:52.692
But what if it's the whole
Macbeth thing?

09:56.697 --> 09:58.532
[thunder rumbling]

09:58.599 --> 09:59.767
- Like I said,

09:59.833 --> 10:01.402
you can hold me responsible
for some of this,

10:01.469 --> 10:02.603
but the whole "bring her
to Paris"

10:02.670 --> 10:03.904
was not your best idea.

10:03.971 --> 10:05.439
- Well,
what was I supposed to do?

10:05.506 --> 10:07.775
- Uh, I don't know.
Tell her? Train her yourself.

10:07.842 --> 10:09.142
- I had no choice.

10:09.209 --> 10:10.510
- Oh, you had lots of choices.

10:10.577 --> 10:12.479
Like who you fell in love with.

10:12.546 --> 10:14.081
- I will not discuss this
with you.

10:14.147 --> 10:15.449
- Seems like we are, though.

10:15.516 --> 10:16.717
The same argument
we've been having

10:16.783 --> 10:19.019
for, I don't know, 15 years?

10:19.085 --> 10:21.188
- Let's stay on task.

10:21.255 --> 10:22.957
The Scottish play
was never supposed to be

10:23.023 --> 10:24.258
performed by a Wizen.

10:24.324 --> 10:25.525
- Well, it's not like
I can control

10:25.592 --> 10:27.561
the Paris Opera Ballet
School syllabus.

10:27.628 --> 10:30.263
- Can you control your sarcasm,
though? It's getting old.

10:30.330 --> 10:32.500
- Oh, no.
Can't seem to. Sorry.

10:32.566 --> 10:34.368
It just rolls out of me
like magic.

10:34.435 --> 10:35.936
- I have to call in
the Paris chapter.

10:36.003 --> 10:37.571
The spell itself
is over 400 years old.

10:37.638 --> 10:40.474
It's gonna take a whole lot
of Wizen power to counter.

10:40.540 --> 10:41.709
- Call them up.

10:41.775 --> 10:43.043
Make sure you let them know
it's you, though.

10:43.110 --> 10:44.111
I am just
an innocent bystander.

10:44.177 --> 10:46.513
- Will you stop this?

10:46.580 --> 10:48.282
My daughter's about
to dance a curse,

10:48.349 --> 10:49.816
and you're gonna have
to take charge!

10:49.883 --> 10:51.418
- [scoffs]

10:51.485 --> 10:53.219
Excuse me.
I'm what?

10:53.286 --> 10:54.955
- Going to have to take charge.

10:55.022 --> 10:57.424
- [shudders]
One more time?

10:57.490 --> 10:58.258
- Charge.

10:58.325 --> 11:00.427
- Oh, why is that?

11:00.494 --> 11:02.696
- Because I'm neutral
on curses.

11:02.763 --> 11:04.365
- One more time, louder.

11:04.431 --> 11:05.966
- Neutral!
On curses.

11:06.033 --> 11:08.368
- Oh!
I'm better at them than you.

11:08.435 --> 11:09.369
Got it!

11:09.436 --> 11:12.273
- The monster is bad at curses.

11:12.339 --> 11:13.840
What a paradox.

11:13.907 --> 11:16.009
- Finally!
[gasps]

11:16.076 --> 11:19.012
Wizens!
[chuckles]

11:19.079 --> 11:21.548
[upbeat suspenseful music]

11:21.615 --> 11:22.983
Well, don't just sit there,
Liz.

11:23.050 --> 11:25.886
We've got a mission
to accomplish.

11:25.953 --> 11:27.721
I'm in charge.

11:27.788 --> 11:28.722
♪♪ ♪♪

11:28.789 --> 11:30.724
[magical shimmering]

11:30.791 --> 11:34.595
♪♪ ♪♪

11:34.661 --> 11:37.597
[ominous music]

11:37.664 --> 11:44.671
♪♪ ♪♪

11:56.449 --> 11:58.786
FINN: Want to feel the calm?

11:58.852 --> 12:01.154
- Yeah, thanks.

12:04.191 --> 12:10.097
♪♪ ♪♪

12:10.164 --> 12:12.833
- Feel the calm.

12:12.900 --> 12:13.867
♪♪ ♪♪

12:13.934 --> 12:15.469
Thanks.

12:15.536 --> 12:16.837
And now get
out of my dance space

12:16.903 --> 12:18.772
before I flatten you.

12:18.839 --> 12:20.874
♪♪ ♪♪

12:20.941 --> 12:23.610
- Please let everything
be okay.

12:23.677 --> 12:28.148
♪♪ ♪♪

12:28.215 --> 12:29.816
Your Majesty.

12:29.883 --> 12:32.753
- I hope you like the flowers.

12:32.820 --> 12:34.154
- The what?

12:34.221 --> 12:37.191
♪♪ ♪♪

12:37.257 --> 12:39.059
- I'm sorry about the gala.

12:39.126 --> 12:43.129
I took some bad advice,
but I was wrong to lie to you.

12:43.196 --> 12:45.232
I'm sorry.

12:45.299 --> 12:47.267
- Everyone's been acting
a little off lately,

12:47.334 --> 12:50.337
not quite like themselves,
myself included.

12:50.404 --> 12:53.374
Let's just call it
the Scottish curse.

12:53.441 --> 12:57.444
Apology accepted.
- Thank you.

12:57.511 --> 13:00.113
♪♪ ♪♪

13:00.180 --> 13:01.448
- I like you.

13:01.515 --> 13:04.551
So can we just
stop being weird?

13:04.618 --> 13:08.688
- I would very much like us
to not be weird.

13:08.755 --> 13:10.657
- Hi.
Eyes on me.

13:10.724 --> 13:12.292
Big show tonight.

13:12.359 --> 13:15.029
Let's just back this up into
a more appropriate distance?

13:15.095 --> 13:16.296
Yeah?

13:16.363 --> 13:18.666
Benoit, the stage manager
needs you, like,

13:18.733 --> 13:20.067
forever ago.

13:20.134 --> 13:24.104
♪♪ ♪♪

13:24.171 --> 13:27.107
[suspenseful music]

13:27.174 --> 13:30.444
♪♪ ♪♪

13:30.511 --> 13:32.379
- Uh, okay.

13:32.445 --> 13:36.550
I think we've mind-melded
for long enough, weirdo.

13:36.617 --> 13:39.519
- I don't know
why I'm doing this.

13:39.586 --> 13:40.654
- [laughs]

13:40.721 --> 13:44.257
♪♪ ♪♪

13:44.324 --> 13:45.926
- Um, what was that?
CECE: [laughs]

13:45.993 --> 13:47.928
