- [gasps]

14:56.163 --> 14:57.097
- What took you so long?

14:57.164 --> 14:58.499
Do you have any idea

14:58.565 --> 15:00.334
how long I was waiting for you
or someone,

15:00.400 --> 15:03.103
anyone, to come and get me?

15:03.170 --> 15:04.538
- Are you who I think you are?

15:04.604 --> 15:06.440
- I'm Juliet!
[words echoing]

15:06.506 --> 15:09.243
And before I got stuck
in this hole,

15:09.309 --> 15:11.378
I was a nomadic Wizen.

15:11.445 --> 15:13.680
I traveled from village
to village

15:13.747 --> 15:16.917
with my caravan
of magical tricks.

15:16.984 --> 15:18.552
I had a really good act.

15:18.619 --> 15:21.622
I was quite the performer,
if I do say so myself.

15:21.688 --> 15:24.591
[chuckles]
I had a great life.

15:24.658 --> 15:27.694
[laughing]
I was so happy!

15:27.761 --> 15:28.895
[sniffles]

15:28.962 --> 15:31.699
But then
he stole my livelihood.

15:31.765 --> 15:34.768
He took everything from me,
word for word,

15:34.835 --> 15:36.771
the whole story...

15:36.837 --> 15:39.606
so I cursed his play.

15:39.673 --> 15:41.742
I should have let
well enough alone,

15:41.809 --> 15:43.644
but oh, no.

15:43.710 --> 15:47.648
I had to listen
to my stupid ego.

15:47.715 --> 15:49.149
I went to opening night

15:49.216 --> 15:51.618
just so that I could laugh
in his face,

15:51.685 --> 15:54.588
but I fell prey
to my own curse.

15:54.655 --> 16:00.494
I've tried haunting theaters,
scaring off actors, but oh, no.

16:00.561 --> 16:04.732
Those thespians, always with
"the show must go on " crap.

16:04.798 --> 16:10.037
You know, I never want to hear
or see Macbeth again!

16:10.103 --> 16:11.571
- Just to be clear,
you're talking about--

16:11.638 --> 16:14.942
- William "Wordsmith"
Shakespeare.

16:15.008 --> 16:16.677
And let me just say
for the record,

16:16.743 --> 16:20.413
in real life,
he's a bit of a jerk.

16:20.480 --> 16:23.350
I have been trapped
in this curse

16:23.416 --> 16:28.856
for 400 years!
[words echoing]

16:28.922 --> 16:32.726
But you, my little Wizen,

16:32.792 --> 16:36.030
are going to set me free.

16:36.096 --> 16:37.731
[laughing]
Yes!

16:37.798 --> 16:39.266
[laughs]

16:39.333 --> 16:42.369
[energetic orchestral music]
[applause]

16:42.436 --> 16:45.071
[Saint-Saens' "Danse Macabre"]

16:45.138 --> 16:52.345
♪♪ ♪♪

17:35.022 --> 17:37.123
JULIET:
Come here, little Wizen!

17:37.190 --> 17:38.625
[applause]
[laughs]

17:38.692 --> 17:40.928
- Something's happening.
I think I did something bad.

17:40.994 --> 17:42.062
We have to stop the ballet.

17:42.129 --> 17:44.365
- It's fine.
It's just nerves.

17:44.431 --> 17:47.901
See? Everything's fine.
You're dancing, I'm dancing.

17:47.968 --> 17:50.404
Mia's queening. It's all good.

17:50.471 --> 17:53.774
[feedback-like screeching]

17:54.208 --> 17:56.743
[wheels creaking]

17:56.810 --> 17:59.613
JULIET: [laughing deliriously]

17:59.679 --> 18:02.883
[gasps and inhales deeply]
You have to complete the spell.

18:02.950 --> 18:05.219
It's our destiny!
[laughs]

18:05.285 --> 18:08.722
Everyone thinks the curse
of Macbeth is bad luck.

18:08.789 --> 18:13.427
I'm the bad luck.
I'm the one haunting the play.

18:13.494 --> 18:17.031
Do you know how many times
I've watched this play?

18:17.097 --> 18:20.767
Every single time
it's performed!

18:20.834 --> 18:22.469
I can't take it anymore!

18:22.536 --> 18:27.374
How many times can one man
ruin himself, am I right?

18:27.440 --> 18:28.676
But...

18:28.742 --> 18:33.580
you can break the curse
and set me free!

18:33.647 --> 18:34.681
[laughs]

18:34.748 --> 18:37.884
It must be done on stage
while performing.

18:37.951 --> 18:38.886
[chuckles]

18:38.952 --> 18:40.287
Actors can't cast a spell

18:40.353 --> 18:44.691
'cause, you know,
they're actors, not Wizens.

18:44.758 --> 18:46.861
[laughs]

18:46.927 --> 18:48.129
Whoo!

18:48.195 --> 18:52.233
I cannot believe
it took 400 years,

18:52.299 --> 18:56.604
but finally,
a Wizen cast as a witch

18:56.670 --> 18:58.605
to set me free!

18:58.672 --> 19:01.641
[laughs excitedly]

19:02.910 --> 19:08.648
And you won't tell a soul,
will you, little girl?

19:08.715 --> 19:10.383
Ooh?

19:10.450 --> 19:13.220
[laughs]

19:13.287 --> 19:15.055
[laughter echoing]

19:15.121 --> 19:17.424
WIZENS: Double, double,
